strikes in Education
Larry reported discovering, as did
Oglesby, that “fantastic strikes“ have
been taken in the area of education
throughout Cuba. “All children — both
in the city and in the country — are
now in school full time," Larry said.
Children Start to school in Cuba on a
level comparable to American kindergarten. Throughout primary school,
children are encouraged to begin developing fields or “interests" which will
eventually be chancellor into prepare'
tion for future occupations. By the time
children enter secondary schools, they
have deﬁnew several “interests" more
completely, and join “circles oi interests” With other students These “circles" then meet regularly with a teacher
or resource advisor for extracurricular
discussions of their interest field.
“Circle" meetings continue through
the preUniversity level, by which time
each student is expected to have refined his particular interest to the level
of sophisticated study which is characteristic oi a “major in an American
college. Participation in “circles" is officially voluntary but it is at the same
time both a somewhat - presented
“norm," and also a prerequisite for ad.
mission to a University.
Larry commented that his initial impression of the human University was
that it is “like universities everywhere"
in terms oi atmosphere and general
characteristics or the student body. One
aspect oi the University which Larry
later discovered is that each University
is also a modified military base of sorts.
Every student has a gun and is assigned
to a squad of students organized by one
leader for the purpose ui modification in
the event pi emergency situations requiring the defense oi the country, city,
or University area.
Each Class of 3040 students is also
organized under a single leader, who
serves as class spokesman, discussion
leader, and general madison between the
class and the professor. in addition, each
class is divided into two equal groups,
which compete dramatically during the
school year for the “honor" or being
granted a greater amount of “voluntary
labor” at the time or preventing crops.
Larry noted that the majority of University processors are very young, and
that the government has apparently not
yet been able to completely overcome
a serious lack of educators. An instructor for a one-year course in humanities,
for example, is likely to have as prepare
union only a six-month training period
in his field.
Although no philosophy “department"
as such experts in human Universities,
there are required philosophy courses
in MarxistrLeninist thought for every departmental field. “An interesting highlight," added Larry, “is the fact that
human Universities have by now completely discussed initially-used Russian
texts on largest-Leninist philosophy as
interior in content and intellectual appeal, and are now using their own text!
on the subject in the University."
Style of fire Spare, Few injuries
